This paper discusses the issue of expressing temporal properties in model checking technologies, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper proposes a set of specification patterns for real-time requirements, which involves the use of formal languages and logic (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of model checking tools for verification, which is a topic related to logic and verification (cs.LO). The paper focuses on the design of reactive systems, which is a topic related to control systems and robotics (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes an integrated tool chain for model checking, which involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI).
